<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910308-0041</DOCNO><DOCID>910308-0041.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Goody Products Inc.:   Loss in the Fourth Period   Narrowed to $2.8 Million</HL><DATE>03/08/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   GOOD</CO><IN>COSMETICS, PERSONAL CARE, OVER-THE-COUNTER REMEDIES (COS)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Goody Products Inc. reported a narrower fourth-quarterloss, reflecting continuing efforts to reduce costs andstreamline manufacturing.   The Kearny, N.J., maker of hair accessories and cosmeticproducts had a loss of $2.8 million, or 43 cents a share,compared with a loss of $7.8 million, or $1.19 a share, ayear ago. Sales were down slightly to $39.9 million from$40.7 million.</LP><TEXT>   For the year, profit was $1.5 million, or 23 cents ashare, compared to a 1989 loss of $5.4 million, or 83 cents ashare. Full-year sales fell to $214.8 million from $220.9million.   &quot;Contributing to profits,&quot; said Leonard Goodman, chairmanand chief executive officer, &quot;was the success of ourcontinuing cost reduction, manufacturing realignment andautomation programs, as well as reduced obsolescence.&quot;</TEXT></DOC>